            "text_truth": {
              "type": "cs-basic-text",
              "settings": {
                "content": "<p>What I discovered was both eye-opening and frustrating. The cosmetics industry has convinced us that skincare needs to be complicated, but <strong>most modern products actually disrupt our skin's natural barrier function.<\/strong><\/p><p>Here's what I learned: Human skin is made up of sebum (natural oils) that contain many of the same fatty acids found in tallow. When we strip away these natural oils with harsh cleansers and then try to replace them with synthetic ingredients, we create a cycle of dependence.<\/p><p><strong>My skin wasn't defective—it was confused.<\/strong> All those products were sending mixed signals to my skin's natural repair systems.<\/p><p>Tallow, on the other hand, is biocompatible. It contains vitamins A, D, E, and K, plus essential fatty acids that human skin recognizes and can actually use. <strong>It's not about adding more chemicals—it's about giving your skin what it naturally understands.<\/strong><\/p><p>That's when I decided to try pure, grass-fed beef tallow.<\/p>"
              }
            },
